.TH "PYFORDPASS" "1" "May 31, 2026" "0.0.0" "pyfordpass"
.SH NAME
pyfordpass \- pyfordpass v0.0.0
.sp
FordPass client and CLI.
.SH INSTALLATION
.INDENT 0.0
.INDENT 3.5
.sp
.EX
pip install pyfordpass
.EE
.UNINDENT
.UNINDENT
.sp
Or with \fBuv\fP:
.INDENT 0.0
.INDENT 3.5
.sp
.EX
uv tool install pyfordpass
.EE
.UNINDENT
.UNINDENT
.SH QUICK START
.sp
The CLI is the primary surface. The library lives behind it for callers who want to integrate
against the same protocol the CLI uses.
.INDENT 0.0
.INDENT 3.5
.sp
.EX
pyfordpass auth signin
pyfordpass vehicle list
pyfordpass remote start
.EE
.UNINDENT
.UNINDENT
.sp
For programmatic use, see \fI\%fordpass.client.AsyncFordPassClient\fP (async HTTP client) and
\fI\%fordpass.sansio.FordPassClient\fP (sans\-I/O protocol core that builds
\fI\%fordpass.sansio.RequestDict\fP descriptors).
