.sp
Manage recurring remote\-start schedules.
.sp
Usage
.INDENT 0.0
.INDENT 3.5
.sp
.EX
pyfordpass schedule [OPTIONS] COMMAND [ARGS]...
.EE
.UNINDENT
.UNINDENT
.SS add
.sp
Add a new recurring remote\-start schedule.
.sp
Usage
.INDENT 0.0
.INDENT 3.5
.sp
.EX
pyfordpass schedule add [OPTIONS] [VIN]
.EE
.UNINDENT
.UNINDENT
.sp
Options
.INDENT 0.0
.TP
.B \-d, \-\-debug
Enable debug level logging.
.UNINDENT
.INDENT 0.0
.TP
.B \-\-start <start>
\fBRequired\fP When the engine should fire \- ISO 8601 (e.g. 2026\-05\-28T13:50:00\-04:00) or \(dqYYYY\-MM\-DD HH:MM\(dq in the timezone given by \-\-tz.
.UNINDENT
.INDENT 0.0
.TP
.B \-\-tz <tz>
Timezone for the schedule: IANA name (e.g. America/New_York), an integer Ford zone code, or \(dqlocal\(dq / unset to use the system timezone.
.UNINDENT
.INDENT 0.0
.TP
.B \-\-days <days>
\fBRequired\fP Days when the schedule fires. Accepts comma\- / space\- / slash\-separated tokens \- full names, abbreviations, or one\-letter shortcuts (e.g. \(dqmon,tue,thu\(dq, \(dqM T Th\(dq, \(dqmwf\(dq).
.UNINDENT
.sp
Arguments
.INDENT 0.0
.TP
.B VIN
Optional argument
.UNINDENT
